+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014qPhCoQyGWMA3Yr64wBMRy","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me create a detailed report:\n\n## Comprehensive Event-Driven Order Processing System Overview\n\n### 1. SOURCE FILES STRUCTURE\n\n#### **src/index.ts** - Main Exports\nCentral barrel file that exports all public APIs from the system.\n\n**Key Exports:**\n- EventBus, ORDER_EVENTS, event types\n- OrderRepository, OrderService, Order-related types\n- InventoryRepository, InventoryService\n- BillingService, calculateOrderTotal\n- NotificationService\n\n---\n\n### 2. EVENTS SUBSYSTEM\n\n#### **src/events/types.ts** - Event Type Definitions\nDefines all event interfaces and constants for the event-driven system.\n\n**Key Interfaces:**\n```typescript\nexport interface OrderEvent {\n  orderId: string;\n  timestamp: number;\n}\n\nexport interface OrderCreatedEvent extends OrderEvent {\n  items: Array<{ productId: string; quantity: number; unitPrice: number }>;\n  customerId: string;\n}\n\nexport interface OrderCancelledEvent extends OrderEvent {\n  reason: string;\n}\n\nexport interface OrderRefundedEvent extends OrderEvent {\n  amount: number;\n}\n\nexport interface PaymentChargedEvent extends OrderEvent {\n  amount: number;\n  paymentMethod: string;\n}\n\nexport interface StockReservedEvent extends OrderEvent {\n  items: Array<{ productId: string; quantity: number }>;\n}\n```\n\n**Event Constants:**\n```javascript\nORDER_EVENTS = {\n  CREATED: 'order.created',\n  CONFIRMED: 'order.confirmed',\n  CANCELLED: 'order.cancelled',\n  REFUNDED: 'order.refunded',\n  PAYMENT_CHARGED: 'order.payment.charged',\n  STOCK_RESERVED: 'order.stock.reserved',\n  STOCK_RELEASED: 'order.stock.released',\n  NOTIFICATION_SENT: 'order.notification.sent'\n}\n```\n\n#### **src/events/bus.ts** - Event Bus Implementation\nImplements publish/subscribe pattern with global handler registry.\n\n**Key Class: EventBus**\n- `on(event: string, handler: EventHandler)` - Register event handler\n- `off(event: string, handler: EventHandler)` - Unregister handler\n- `emit(event: string, data: unknown)` - Emit event to all registered handlers (async)\n- `clear()` - Clear all handlers\n\nNote: Uses module-level `globalHandlers` Map shared across all EventBus instances.\n\n---\n\n### 3. ORDERS SUBSYSTEM\n\n#### **src/orders/repository.ts** - Order Data Layer\nManages order persistence in an in-memory Map store.\n\n**Key Types:**\n```typescript\nexport type OrderStatus = 'pending' | 'confirmed' | 'cancelled' | 'refunded';\n\nexport interface OrderItem {\n  productId: string;\n  quantity: number;\n  unitPrice: number;\n}\n\nexport interface Order {\n  id: string;\n  customerId: string;\n  items: OrderItem[];\n  status: OrderStatus;\n  total: number;\n  discount: number;\n  taxRate: number;\n  createdAt: number;\n  updatedAt: number;\n  notes?: string;\n}\n```\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `create(order: Order): Order` - Create new order\n- `findById(id: string): Order | undefined` - Retrieve by ID\n- `update(id: string, updates: Partial<Order>): Order | undefined` - Partial update with auto-timestamp\n- `findByCustomer(customerId: string): Order[]` - Find all orders for a customer\n- `findByStatus(status: OrderStatus): Order[]` - Find orders by status\n- `clear(): void` - Reset store\n\n#### **src/orders/service.ts** - Order Business Logic\nOrchestrates the order lifecycle through events.\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- OrderRepository\n- EventBus\n- BillingService\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `createOrder(id, customerId, items, discount?, taxRate?): Promise<Order>` - Creates order, emits ORDER_CREATED, charges payment, confirms\n- `cancelOrder(id, reason): Promise<Order | undefined>` - Emits CANCELLED event, updates status (only if confirmed)\n- `refundOrder(id): Promise<Order | undefined>` - Issues refund within 30-day window, updates status\n- `getOrder(id): Order | undefined` - Retrieves order\n- `getOrdersByCustomer(customerId): Order[]` - Gets customer's orders\n\n**Constants:**\n- `REFUND_WINDOW_DAYS = 30` - Refund eligibility period\n\n---\n\n### 4. INVENTORY SUBSYSTEM\n\n#### **src/inventory/repository.ts** - Stock Management Data Layer\nIn-memory store tracking product stock availability and reservations.\n\n**Key Type:**\n```typescript\nexport interface StockRecord {\n  productId: string;\n  available: number;\n  reserved: number;\n}\n```\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `setStock(productId, available): void` - Set initial stock (preserves reservations)\n- `getStock(productId): StockRecord | undefined` - Retrieve stock info\n- `reserve(productId, quantity): boolean` - Reserve quantity if available\n- `release(productId, quantity): boolean` - Release reserved quantity\n- `clear(): void` - Reset store\n\n#### **src/inventory/service.ts** - Stock Reservation Logic\nEvent-driven inventory management. Listens to ORDER_CREATED and ORDER_CANCELLED events.\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- InventoryRepository\n- EventBus\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `registerHandlers(): void` - Register event listeners\n- `handleOrderCreated(data): Promise<void>` (private) - Reserves stock for all order items with rollback on failure\n- `handleOrderCancelled(data): Promise<void>` (private) - Releases reserved stock, emits STOCK_RELEASED\n- `setStock(productId, quantity): void` - Wrapper for repository\n- `getStock(productId)` - Wrapper for repository\n\n---\n\n### 5. BILLING SUBSYSTEM\n\n#### **src/billing/calculator.ts** - Price Calculation Logic\nPure function for computing order totals with discounts and taxes.\n\n**Key Type:**\n```typescript\nexport interface PriceBreakdown {\n  subtotal: number;\n  discountAmount: number;\n  taxAmount: number;\n  total: number;\n}\n```\n\n**Key Function:**\n```typescript\ncalculateOrderTotal(\n  items: OrderItem[],\n  discountPercent: number,\n  taxRate: number\n): PriceBreakdown\n```\n- Calculates subtotal from items\n- Applies percentage discount before tax\n- Calculates tax on post-discount amount\n- Returns rounded price breakdown\n- Precision: Math.round(...*100)/100 to handle penny calculations\n\n#### **src/billing/service.ts** - Payment Processing\nManages payment charging and refunds. Integrates with NotificationService.\n\n**Key Type:**\n```typescript\nexport interface PaymentRecord {\n  orderId: string;\n  amount: number;\n  method: string;\n  status: 'charged' | 'refunded';\n  processedAt: number;\n}\n```\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- EventBus\n- NotificationService\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `registerHandlers(): void` - Register event listeners (STOCK_RESERVED, REFUNDED)\n- `chargePayment(orderId, items, discountPercent, taxRate, paymentMethod): Promise<PaymentRecord>` - Charges payment, records it, sends confirmation\n- `issueRefund(orderId, amount): Promise<PaymentRecord | undefined>` - Issues refund, emits REFUNDED event\n- `getPayment(orderId): PaymentRecord | undefined` - Retrieves payment record\n- `clear(): void` - Reset payment store\n\n---\n\n### 6. NOTIFICATIONS SUBSYSTEM\n\n#### **src/notifications/service.ts** - Notification Delivery\nManages notification templates and tracks sent notifications.\n\n**Key Type:**\n```typescript\nexport interface NotificationRecord {\n  type: string;\n  orderId: string;\n  message: string;\n  sentAt: number;\n}\n```\n\n**Templates:**\n- `'order.confirmed'`: \"Your order {orderId} has been confirmed. Total: ${total}\"\n- `'order.cancelled'`: \"Your order {orderId} has been cancelled. Reason: {reason}\"\n- `'order.refunded'`: \"Your refund of ${amount} for order {orderId} has been processed.\"\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `sendConfirmation(orderId, total): NotificationRecord` - Sends order confirmation\n- `sendCancellation(orderId, reason): NotificationRecord` - Sends cancellation notice\n- `sendRefundNotice(orderId, amount): NotificationRecord` - Sends refund notice\n- `getSentNotifications(): NotificationRecord[]` - Returns copy of all sent notifications\n- `clear(): void` - Reset sent notifications\n\n---\n\n### 7. TEST FILES STRUCTURE\n\n#### **tests/events.test.ts** - EventBus Tests\nLocation: `/workspace/tests/events.test.ts`\n\n**Test Coverage:**\n- Event emission to registered handlers\n- Multiple handlers for same event\n- Events don't fire for different listeners\n- Handler removal with `off()`\n- Clearing all handlers\n\n#### **tests/orders.test.ts** - Order Service & Repository Tests\nLocation: `/workspace/tests/orders.test.ts`\n\n**Test Coverage (OrderService - 7 tests):**\n- Order creation and confirmation\n- Stock reservation on order creation\n- Order cancellation (confirmed orders only)\n- Stock release on cancellation\n- Refusal to cancel non-confirmed orders\n- Refund within 30-day window\n- Refund allowed on day 30 exactly\n- Refund rejection after 30 days\n\n**Test Coverage (OrderRepository - 4 tests):**\n- Create and retrieve order\n- Update preserves other fields\n- Returns undefined for missing order\n- Find orders by customer\n\n#### **tests/inventory.test.ts** - Inventory Service Tests\nLocation: `/workspace/tests/inventory.test.ts`\n\n**Test Coverage:**\n- Stock reservation on ORDER_CREATED event\n- Throws error when stock insufficient\n- Rolls back partial reservations on failure (transactional behavior)\n- Releases stock on ORDER_CANCELLED event\n- Handles concurrent orders independently\n\n#### **tests/billing.test.ts** - Price Calculation & Billing Service Tests\nLocation: `/workspace/tests/billing.test.ts`\n\n**Test Coverage (calculateOrderTotal - 4 tests):**\n- Total calculation with no discount/tax\n- Percentage discount applied before tax\n- Multiple items with discount and tax\n- Correct rounding for penny-edge amounts\n\n**Test Coverage (BillingService - 4 tests):**\n- Payment charging and recording\n- Confirmation notification on charge\n- Refund issuance and status update\n- Refund notification sending\n\n#### **tests/notifications.test.ts** - Notification Service Tests\nLocation: `/workspace/tests/notifications.test.ts`\n\n**Test Coverage:**\n- Order confirmation sending\n- Cancellation notice sending\n- Refund notice sending\n- Tracking all sent notifications\n\n---\n\n### 8. OVERALL ARCHITECTURE & DATA FLOW\n\n#### **Order Creation Flow:**\n```\nOrderService.createOrder()\n  → OrderRepository.create() [status: pending]\n  → EventBus.emit(ORDER_CREATED)\n    ├→ InventoryService.handleOrderCreated()\n    │   ├→ InventoryRepository.reserve() for each item\n    │   └→ EventBus.emit(STOCK_RESERVED)\n    └→ (other handlers)\n  → BillingService.chargePayment()\n    ├→ calculateOrderTotal()\n    ├→ PaymentRecord stored\n    └→ NotificationService.sendConfirmation()\n  → OrderRepository.update() [status: confirmed, total set]\n  → EventBus.emit(ORDER_CONFIRMED)\n```\n\n#### **Order Cancellation Flow:**\n```\nOrderService.cancelOrder()\n  → EventBus.emit(ORDER_CANCELLED, { items })\n    └→ InventoryService.handleOrderCancelled()\n        ├→ InventoryRepository.release() for each item\n        └→ EventBus.emit(STOCK_RELEASED)\n  → OrderRepository.update() [status: cancelled]\n```\n\n#### **Order Refund Flow:**\n```\nOrderService.refundOrder()\n  → Validate: within 30-day window\n  → BillingService.issueRefund()\n    ├→ PaymentRecord.status = 'refunded'\n    ├→ EventBus.emit(ORDER_REFUNDED)\n    │   └→ BillingService.handleRefund()\n    │       └→ NotificationService.sendRefundNotice()\n    └→ NotificationService.sendRefundNotice()\n  → OrderRepository.update() [status: refunded]\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. KEY TYPES & INTERFACES SUMMARY\n\n| Type | Module | Purpose |\n|------|--------|---------|\n| `OrderEvent` | events/types | Base event interface |\n| `OrderCreatedEvent` | events/types | Order creation event with items |\n| `OrderCancelledEvent` | events/types | Order cancellation with reason |\n| `OrderRefundedEvent` | events/types | Refund event with amount |\n| `PaymentChargedEvent` | events/types | Payment charged with method |\n| `StockReservedEvent` | events/types | Stock reservation confirmation |\n| `Order` | orders/repository | Full order object |\n| `OrderItem` | orders/repository | Item in order |\n| `OrderStatus` | orders/repository | State: pending\\|confirmed\\|cancelled\\|refunded |\n| `StockRecord` | inventory/repository | Available and reserved stock |\n| `PriceBreakdown` | billing/calculator | Itemized price calculation |\n| `PaymentRecord` | billing/service | Payment transaction record |\n| `NotificationRecord` | notifications/service | Sent notification log entry |\n\n---\n\n### 10. BUILD & TEST CONFIGURATION\n\n**Package.json Scripts:**\n- `npm run build` - Compiles TypeScript (tsc)\n- `npm run lint` - ESLint checks\n- `npm test` - Vitest runs all tests\n\n**TypeScript Config:**\n- Target: ES2022\n- Module: Node16 (ESM)\n- Strict mode: enabled\n- Output: ./dist\n- Source: ./src\n\n**Total Test Count:** 30 visible tests across 5 test files\n\n---\n\nThis is a well-structured event-driven system with clear separation of concerns, using a pub/sub event bus to decouple order, inventory, billing, and notification services."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ac41053 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 31907\ntool_uses: 22\nduration_ms: 40825</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"57ab05b4-d29f-4a8c-b87c-21922c75fd94","uuid":"e3773c34-a711-4f5a-bf85-f1984375ef2e","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the full codebase structure of this event-driven order processing system. I need to understand:\n1. All source files under src/ and their purposes\n2. All test files and their locations\n3. The overall architecture: events, orders, inventory, billing, notifications\n4. Key types/interfaces used across the system\n\nGive me a comprehensive overview with file paths and key functions/classes in each file.","agentId":"ac41053","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me